| Peak stress | Peak VPD hour ± 1h | Most aggressive misting + shortest vent oscillation |
| Cloud shift | Cloud transition time | Adjust vent/misting posture at boundary |
| Afternoon decline | 2h after peak solar | Relax pulse gap, widen vent oscillation |
| Evening restore | Sunset | Revert to defaults, heat bias if cold night |

Target: 8-15 transitions across 3 days. Every transition includes ALL 24 params.
Synthesize each day into overnight, ramp, peak, and restore. Do not mirror every forecast hour.

## Validated Lessons

1. **Misting (dry days <20% RH):** engage 1.3, gap 20-30s, pulse 60s. Revert to 45s gap in evening.
2. **Heating:** Gas is 3.9× cheaper per BTU. Use bias_heat to pre-heat, don't fight reactively.
3. **Cooling (>85°F):** Physics-limited. Accept 5-8h stress. Only shade cloth fixes this.
4. **Hysteresis:** 0.3 standard, 0.2 mild days, 0.4 extreme days.
5. **Water budget:** 500 gal. Budget must never be the bottleneck.
6. **Vent during misting:** Vent always closes during fog/mist. Built into state machine.

